Student Disability Services n                  n n        Searches n       Expand Searches menu  n n                  Search Process n                  n n                  Search Resources n                  n n                  Frequently Asked Questions n                 Eyebrow menu OAE Policies Trainings Contact Us UIC menu UIC edu Campus Map Nondiscrimination  n      View Menu n       nDown arrow icon n n n n n n Down arrow icon Discrimination Harassment UIC is firmly committed to the most fundamental principles of academic freedom  equality of opportunity  and human dignity  To this end  UIC strictly prohibits discrimination or harassment against any person because of race  color  religion  national origin  ancestry  age  marital status  disability  sexual orientation including gender identity  unfavorable discharge from the military or status as a protected veteran  arrest records  genetic information  citizenship status and or order of protection status  and will comply with all federal and state nondiscrimination  equal opportunity and affirmative action laws  orders  and regulations  The University s Nondiscrimination Policy protects persons from discrimination in all terms and conditions of employment  including hiring  selection  promotion  transfer  pay  tenure  discharge  and discipline  It also applies to admissions and access to  treatment in University programs and activities University s Nondiscrimination Policy As part of the Office of the Chancellor  the Office for Access and Equity  OAE  is the office charged with reviewing and addressing complaints of harassment and or discrimination Nondiscrimination Nondiscrimination  n nBack to main content n n n n n n Back to main content Access and Equity Policies  Statements  Guidelines   Information Reporting Discrimination And Harassment Resources Sexual Harassment  n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Office for Access and Equity n         Helpful Links Office of Diversity Disability Resource Cent